        <num>CC 3049</num>
        <heading>3049.  Surety's right of reimbursement for payment of obligation</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3049.  Surety's right of reimbursement for payment of obligation
A surety who pays the creditor is entitled to reimbursement from the principal obligor.  He may not recover reimbursement until the principal obligation is due and exigible.
A surety for multiple solidary obligors may recover from any of them reimbursement of the whole amount he has paid the creditor.</p>
        </content>
